SHAWNEE STATE BANK et al. v. Hal M. CANNON, Trustee of the Estate of J. S. MULLEN, Bankrupt, et al. No. 307. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. Jan. 13, 1931. Potterf, Gray & Poindexter, Dolman & Dyer, and Slough & Gibson, all of Ardmore, Okl., for appellants. Ledbetter & Ledbetter, Sigler & Jackson, and J. B. Moore, all of Ardmore, Okl., for appellees.

’Before LEWIS and MeDERMOTT, Circuit Judges, and KENNEDY, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed January 13, 1931, on motion of appellant.
